meaningMnemonic: You already know that 弦楽 means "string music," so add some <kanji>pipe</kanji>s to that, like trumpets and saxophones, and you'll have <vocabulary>orchestral music</vocabulary>. You can't have a whole orchestra with just the string section!
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word that uses the on'yomi readings of the kanji. You should be able to read this on your own.
